<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
================================================================================
  FS25_SlurryPipeSystem — Config Manifest
================================================================================
  Each entry's "path" attribute must EXACTLY match the tail of the runtime
  vehicle/placeable's configFileName (case-insensitive). When the match
  succeeds, SPS loads the bundled fillPoints.xml from:
      configs/<path with the trailing .xml filename stripped>/fillPoints.xml

  Examples:
      path="data/vehicles/kaweco/profi2/profi2.xml"
        -> configs/data/vehicles/kaweco/profi2/fillPoints.xml

      path="FS25_Pichon_BMIX80/BMIX.xml"
        -> configs/FS25_Pichon_BMIX80/fillPoints.xml

  Optional "configFolder" attribute overrides where the bundled fillPoints.xml
  lives. Use this when a mod ships multiple XMLs in the same folder (the
  auto-derived bundled folder would collide), or when you want to organise
  bundled configs differently from the runtime path.

  Example (UK Shed: two placeables share FS25_UKStlyleBuilding/xml/):
      <placeable path="FS25_UKStlyleBuilding/xml/cowShedUK.xml"
                 configFolder="mods/FS25_UKStlyleBuilding/xml/cowShedUK"/>
        -> configs/mods/FS25_UKStlyleBuilding/xml/cowShedUK/fillPoints.xml

  Vehicles or placeables that ship with an embedded <slurryPipeSystem> block
  inside their own XML do NOT need a manifest entry. The embedded block wins
  over any manifest entry, scoped to that vehicle instance only.
  
  NOTE: Mod entries use paths WITHOUT "mods/" prefix to support custom mods
  folders. The configFolder attribute retains "mods/" to preserve bundled
  config locations.
================================================================================
-->

